msgid "Signal"
msgstr "Comhartha"

msgid "Instancing with signals"
msgstr "Tionscáil le comharthaí"

msgid ""
"Signals provide a way to decouple game objects, allowing you to avoid "
"forcing a fixed arrangement of nodes. One sign that a signal might be called "
"for is when you find yourself using ``get_parent()``. Referring directly to "
"a node's parent means that you can't easily move that node to another "
"location in the scene tree. This can be especially problematic when you are "
"instancing objects at runtime and may want to place them in an arbitrary "
"location in the running scene tree."
msgstr ""
"Soláthraíonn comharthaí bealach chun rudaí cluiche a dhíchúpláil, rud a "
"ligeann duit socrú seasta de nóid a sheachaint. Comhartha amháin a "
"d’fhéadfaí a iarraidh ar chomhartha ná nuair a bhíonn ``get_parent()`` in "
"úsáid agat. Má dhéanann tú tagairt go díreach do thuismitheoir nód ní féidir "
"leat an nód sin a aistriú go suíomh eile sa chrann radhairc. Féadann sé seo "
"a bheith ina fhadhb go háirithe agus tú ag cur rudaí in airde ag am rite "
"agus b'fhéidir gur mhaith leat iad a chur in ionad treallach sa chrann "
"radharc reatha."

msgid "Below we'll consider an example of such a situation: firing bullets."
msgstr ""
"Anseo thíos déanfaimid sampla de chás den sórt sin a mheas: urchair a "
"lámhach."

msgid "Shooting example"
msgstr "Sampla lámhach"

msgid ""
"Consider a player character that can rotate and shoot towards the mouse. "
"Every time the mouse button is clicked, we create an instance of the bullet "
"at the player's location. See :ref:`doc_instancing` for details."
msgstr ""
"Smaoinigh ar charachtar imreoir atá in ann rothlú agus lámhach i dtreo an "
"luch. Gach uair a chliceáltar an cnaipe luiche, cruthaímid sampla den piléar "
"ag suíomh an imreora. Féach:ref: `doc_instancing` le haghaidh sonraí."

msgid ""
"We'll use an ``Area2D`` for the bullet, which moves in a straight line at a "
"given velocity:"
msgstr ""
"Úsáidfimid ``Area2D`` don piléar, a ghluaiseann i líne dhíreach ag treoluas "
"ar leith:"

msgid ""
"However, if the bullets are added as children of the player, then they will "
"remain \"attached\" to the player as it rotates:"
msgstr ""
"Mar sin féin, má chuirtear na piléir leis mar leanaí an imreora, ansin "
"fanfaidh siad “ceangailte” leis an imreoir de réir mar a rothlaíonn sé:"

msgid ""
"Instead, we need the bullets to be independent of the player's movement - "
"once fired, they should continue traveling in a straight line and the player "
"can no longer affect them. Instead of being added to the scene tree as a "
"child of the player, it makes more sense to add the bullet as a child of the "
"\"main\" game scene, which may be the player's parent or even further up the "
"tree."
msgstr ""
"Ina áit sin, ní mór dúinn go mbeadh na piléir neamhspleách ar ghluaiseacht "
"an imreora - nuair a dhéantar iad a lámhú, ba cheart dóibh leanúint ar "
"aghaidh ag taisteal i líne dhíreach agus ní féidir leis an imreoir tionchar "
"In ionad a chur leis an gcrann radhairc mar leanbh an imreora, bíonn sé níos "
"ciall an piléar a chur leis mar leanbh den “phríomhradharc” cluiche, ar "
"d'fhéadfadh a bheith ina thuismitheoir an imreora nó fiú níos faide suas an "
"crann."

msgid "You could do this by adding the bullet to the main scene directly:"
msgstr ""
"D'fhéadfá é seo a dhéanamh tríd an piléar a chur leis an bpríomh-radharc go "
"díreach:"

msgid ""
"However, this will lead to a different problem. Now if you try to test your "
"\"Player\" scene independently, it will crash on shooting, because there is "
"no parent node to access. This makes it a lot harder to test your player "
"code independently and also means that if you decide to change your main "
"scene's node structure, the player's parent may no longer be the appropriate "
"node to receive the bullets."
msgstr ""
"Mar sin féin, beidh fadhb dhifriúil mar thoradh air seo. Anois má dhéanann "
"tú iarracht do radharc “Player” a thástáil go neamhspleách, tiocfaidh sé ar "
"lámhach, toisc nach bhfuil aon nód tuismitheora ann le rochtain a fháil. "
"Fágann sé seo go bhfuil sé i bhfad níos deacra do chód imreora a thástáil go "
"neamhspleách agus ciallaíonn sé freisin má shocraíonn tú struchtúr nód do "
"phríomhradharc a athrú, b'fhéidir nach mbeidh tuismitheoir an imreora an nód "
"cuí a thuilleadh chun na piléar a fháil."

msgid ""
"The solution to this is to use a signal to \"emit\" the bullets from the "
"player. The player then has no need to \"know\" what happens to the bullets "
"after that - whatever node is connected to the signal can \"receive\" the "
"bullets and take the appropriate action to spawn them."
msgstr ""
"Is é an réiteach ar seo comhartha a úsáid chun na piléir ón imreoir “a "
"astú”. Níl aon ghá ag an imreoir ansin “a fhios” a bheith agat cad a "
"tharlaíonn do na piléir ina dhiaidh sin - is féidir le cibé nód atá "
"ceangailte leis an gcomhartha na piléar “a fháil” agus an gníomh cuí a "
"ghlacadh chun iad a scaoileadh."

